# Installation

## Prerequisites

- **Python {{ python_version }}+**
- **[uv](https://github.com/astral-sh/uv)** — fast Python package manager

## Install

```bash
uv sync
```

This installs the pyarnes packages (pulled from the pyarnes repo via git URLs) plus all dev tooling (ruff, ty, pytest, bandit, etc.).

## Verify installation

```bash
uv run tasks check
```

Expected output: lint and typecheck pass; `test` is a no-op because no `tests/` directory exists yet (see [Quick Start](quickstart.md) for how to scaffold your first test).

## Pulling template updates

When improvements land in the pyarnes template upstream, fold them into this project with a single task:

```bash
uv run tasks update
```

This wraps `copier update` under the hood — you don't need to know Copier's flags. Conflicts (if any) are surfaced interactively.
